# Project-level pnpm config. Cascades over `~/.npmrc` and pnpm's
# user-level config, but loses to `pnpm-workspace.yaml` settings.
#
# global-pnpmfile=
#   Force pnpm to IGNORE any user-level `global-pnpmfile` when running
#   inside this repo. Without this, contributors with a global hook
#   configured (a common supply-chain pattern — see e.g. the same
#   git-block content we now ship in .pnpmfile.cjs) hash a different
#   pnpmfile combination than CI, breaking `--frozen-lockfile` with
#   ERR_PNPM_LOCKFILE_CONFIG_MISMATCH on the `pnpmfileChecksum` field.
#
#   With this set, every machine — yours, mine, CI — sees exactly the
#   same pnpmfile (the project's .pnpmfile.cjs and nothing else), so
#   the checksum recorded in pnpm-lock.yaml matches everywhere and
#   `--frozen-lockfile` works in CI.
#
#   Our project's .pnpmfile.cjs already implements the git-block hook
#   most people put in their global pnpmfile, so contributors aren't
#   losing protection — they're gaining a project-wide guarantee.
global-pnpmfile=
